<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/717484-what-was-wrong-with-dylan-why-was-she-so">What was wrong with Dylan? Why was she so socially awkward and what did she mean when she kept saying that only Zadie knew the real her?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_717484'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F15776309-reconstructing-amelia">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/717484-what-was-wrong-with-dylan-why-was-she-so">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/717484-what-was-wrong-with-dylan-why-was-she-so">See all 3 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/32825993-xosammidxo"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1404608945i/32825993._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/32825993-xosammidxo">xoSammiDxo</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">My take is a mild form of autism, perhaps Asperger&apos;s. Dylan wasn&apos;t socially awkward, she simply didn&apos;t relate to social cues nor did she always provid<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">My take is a mild form of autism, perhaps Asperger's. Dylan wasn't socially awkward, she simply didn't relate to social cues nor did she always provide them. And in a piece it is revealed by Dylan's mom "only her father, me, and Zadie know." this is what is meant by "knew the real her". Zadie knew of the Asperger's, but no one else outside of the immediate family knew.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
